{{Infobox scientist |name = Ferenc Szabadváry |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date|1923|09|01}} |birth_place = |residence = |nationality = [[Hungary|Hungarian]] |death_date = {{death date and age|2006|05|21|1923|09|01}} |death_place = |field = |work_institution = |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = }}
'''Ferenc Szabadváry''' (1 September 1923 – 21 May 2006) was a [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] [[chemist]] and [[historian]]. From 1971 he was director at the [[Hungarian National Museum for Science and Technology]]. He published several books on the history of chemistry and biographies of chemists. He received the [[Dexter Award]] in 1970.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.scs.illinois.edu/~mainzv/HIST/awards/Dexter%20Papers/SzabadvaryBioJJB.pdf | title = Ferenc Szabadváry (1923–2006)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.matud.iif.hu/06aug/14.html| title = Ferenc Szabadváry }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=In Memoriam|journal=Archives Internationales d'Histoire des Sciences|volume=55|issue=155|year=2005|pages=491–503|issn=0003-9810|doi=10.1484/J.ARIHS.5.101643}}</ref>
